# Precision Over Verbosity

## Rules

- Prefer short, explicit statements over long narrative explanations.
- Apply progressive disclosure: present high-level guidance first, then add detail only when needed for decisions, risk control, or requested depth.
- Remove duplicated wording when the same rule already exists in a clearer location.
- Keep README and governance docs focused on repository purpose, structure, and decision boundaries.
- When replacing obsolete material, delete it instead of leaving parallel explanations behind.
- Layer 1 (always-on): AGENTS.md, README.md, 00-overview.mdc — stay under 60 lines total, no background knowledge
- Layer 2 (task-time): agent-iteration-contract.md, skill files — referenced when executing tasks
- Layer 3 (reference): docs/REPOSITORY-GOALS.md and other docs/ files — consulted when needed
- Do not promote layer 3 content into layer 1 files.
